Code snippets

Powershell

Falls man in PowerShell ein Problem beim Ausführen eines Tools hat, hilft folgender Befehl

Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser -ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted

Project Template

Frontend mit jQuery, Bootstrap und Typescript, incl. npm scripts

Zuerst Projekt Struktur erstellen:

git clone https://gitlab.com/rgrueneis/jquerytypescriptproject.git

Danach die Node-Module installieren:

npm install

bzw.

yarn install

WPF

Settings in .csproj file to enable output to console (net5 only)

  <PropertyGroup>
    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>
    <TargetFramework>net5.0-windows</TargetFramework>
    <UseWPF>true</UseWPF>
    <DisableWinExeOutputInference>True</DisableWinExeOutputInference>
  </PropertyGroup>

ConfigurationBuilder

var config = new ConfigurationBuilder()
    .SetBasePath(AppContext.BaseDirectory)
    .AddJsonFile("appsettings.json")
    .Build();

Don't forget to add package:

dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.Json

Set current culture

private void Window_Loaded(object sender, RoutedEventArgs e)
{            
   Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture = new CultureInfo("de-AT");
   //...
}

Database

Tool dotnet-ef

check version

dotnet-ef --version

install latest version

dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef

install specific version net5

dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef --version 5.0.11

install specific version net6

dotnet tool install --global dotnet-ef --version 6.0

update

dotnet tool update --global dotnet-ef

Packages to install from console

net5

dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore --version 5.0.11
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design --version 5.0.11
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools --version 5.0.11
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer --version 5.0.11
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite --version 5.0.11

net6

dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore --version 6.0
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design --version 6.0
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools --version 6.0
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer --version 6.0
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite --version 6.0

Packages to install from Package Manager

  • replace NorthwindDbLib with the name of your lib
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore -ProjectName NorthwindDbLib
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design -ProjectName NorthwindDbLib
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Tools -ProjectName NorthwindDbLib
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer -ProjectName NorthwindDbLib
Install-Package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite -ProjectName NorthwindDbLib

Generate C# classes

Note: Replace C:\Temp with the correct path (try to avoid blanks in the folder name) * for MDF from console:

dotnet ef dbcontext scaffold "Server=(LocalDB)\mssqllocaldb;attachdbfilename=C:\Temp\Northwnd.mdf;integrated security=True;MultipleActiveResultSets=True" Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer -f -c NorthwindContext
  • for Sqlite from console:
dotnet ef dbcontext scaffold "data source=C:\PR\CSharp\PR4\EfDbFirstWpfDemo\NorthwindDbLib\Northwnd.sqlite" Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite -f -c NorthwindContext
  • for MDF from Package Manager:
Scaffold-DbContext "Server=(LocalDB)\mssqllocaldb; attachdbfilename=C:\Temp\Northwnd.mdf;integrated security=True; MultipleActiveResultSets=True" Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer -force -context NorthwindContext
  • for Sqlite from Package Manager:
Scaffold-DbContext "data source=C:\PR\CSharp\PR4\EfDbFirstWpfDemo\NorthwindDbLib\Northwnd.sqlite" Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite -force -context NorthwindContext

Connectionstring in appsettings.json

{
  "ConnectionStrings": {
    "NorthwindDbMdf": "Server=(LocalDB)\\mssqllocaldb; attachdbfilename=C:\\Temp\\Northwnd.mdf;integrated security=True;MultipleActiveResultSets=True",
    "NorthwindDbSqlite": "data source=C:\\Temp\\Northwnd.sqlite"
  }
}
